 they worked from the outset—forgive me for going round the houses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> but it is important to set this background—with the sort of budgetary envelope tha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t was assumed for them by the MO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">J planners. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If you look at the figures, a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lthough they have consistently reduced their costs year on year and are still reducing them, our view—I am talking </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">about </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">my view as an LSB board member now, not as the potential chair of the OLC—is that their cost per case is still too expensive. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 14.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">What we would like to see—</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and what I would like</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to do if I were made chairman—</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">first </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">would be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to capitalise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on their strength of dealing with cases promptly and moving them through the system quickly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> because </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; fon